A. figurata
).

Brief Diagnosis : Vertex slightly exposed. Head with a distinct pale rectangular interantennal macula surround-ed by dark brown margin. Ocelli distinct. Pronotum subparabolic with large ovoid pale macula surrounded by broad brown borders, margin hyaline. Tegmina well developed, with a pair of brown macula. Profemur B 3 . Pulvilli present only in the fourth tarsomere of all legs. Tarsal claws simple, symmetrical. Supra–anal plate entire, symmetrical. Subgenital plate weakly asymmetrical. Styles short, angular. Genital hook ( L3’ ) with a preapical incision; accessory median phallomere ( L4’ ) present with setal brush; the median phallomere L2D’ elongate; L2E’ extended anteriorly, with setal brush;
R 1’
ovoid with two acute lateral teeth;
R 2’
posteriorly rounded two acute lateral teeth;
R 3’
scalartrapezoidal with rounded edges.

